9 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
10 An Act relating to firearms; creating the Municipal
Carry Act; providing short title; amending 21 O.S.
11 2021, Section 1277, which relates to the unlawful
carry of firearms; modifying scope and providing an
12 exception to certain prohibited act; clarifying scope
of lawful carry for certain individuals; authorizing
13 certain carry by judges, elected officials, and
designated employees of a municipality under certain
14 circumstances; providing restrictions; construing
provision; updating statutory language and
15 references; providing for noncodification; and
providing an effective date.
16
17
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
21 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
22 This act shall be known and may be cited as the “Municipal Carry
23 Act”.
24
